edu.biu.scapi.midLayer.asymmetricCrypto.keys

Class ScCramerShoupPublicKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.biu.scapi.midLayer.asymmetricCrypto.keys.ScCramerShoupPublicKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CramerShoupPublicKey, java.io.Serializable, java.security.Key, java.security.PublicKey

    public class ScCramerShoupPublicKey
extends java.lang.Object
implements CramerShoupPublicKey
    This class represents a Public Key suitable for the Cramer Shoup Encryption Scheme. Although the constructor is public, it should only be instantiated by the Encryption Scheme itself via the generateKey function.
    Author:
    Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Yael Ejgenberg)
    See Also:

      • generateSendableData

        public KeySendableData generateSendableData()
        Description copied from interface: CramerShoupPublicKey
        This function is used when a Cramer Shoup Public Key needs to be sent via a Channel or any other means of sending data (including serialization). It retrieves all the data needed to reconstruct this Public Key at a later time and/or in a different VM. It puts all the data in an instance of the relevant class that implements the KeySendableData interface.
        Specified by:
        generateSendableData in interface CramerShoupPublicKey
        Returns:
        the KeySendableData object
